## 1. Governance & Policy
- Establish and maintain the SAM framework (aligned with ISO/IEC 19770 and ITIL).  
- Define organizational roles, responsibilities, and escalation paths.  
- Develop policies for software acquisition, usage, and disposal.  
- Maintain audit readiness and compliance posture.  
- Manage risk and handle exceptions.  
- Oversee vendor and contract governance.  

---

## 2. Inventory & Discovery
- Discover and catalog software assets across all environments.  
- Normalize data from multiple inventory sources (SCCM, Intune, Jamf, etc.).  
- Map software to hardware, users, and departments.  
- Identify unauthorized or shadow IT.  
- Track the software lifecycle from request to retirement.  
- Implement software metering and usage tracking.  

---

## 3. License Management
- Track entitlements, contracts, and proof of purchase.  
- Reconcile licenses with installed software.  
- Optimize license usage (reclaim, downgrade, or reallocate).  
- Manage SaaS, cloud, and hybrid licensing models.  
- Track specialized license types (NUL, CAL, OEM, Academic, etc.).  
- Conduct periodic true-ups and license position reports.  

---

## 4. Procurement & Contract Management
- Standardize software request and approval workflows.  
- Evaluate vendors and negotiate favorable terms.  
- Track purchase orders, invoices, and renewals.  
- Forecast renewals and future spend.  
- Manage contract performance, SLAs, and EULAs.  
- Collaborate with Finance and Legal for cost control and compliance.  

---

## 5. Compliance & Audit Management
- Conduct regular internal compliance assessments.  
- Coordinate external vendor audits (Microsoft, Adobe, IBM, etc.).  
- Maintain audit documentation and evidence repositories.  
- Address non-compliance and implement corrective actions.  
- Continuously monitor compliance across environments.  
- Automate compliance alerts and remediation workflows.  

---

## 6. Optimization & Cost Management
- Implement cost-saving strategies (license re-harvesting, pooling, etc.).  
- Monitor software utilization to identify waste.  
- Evaluate ROI and TCO of software assets.  
- Optimize SaaS subscriptions and cloud licensing.  
- Forecast renewal costs and track savings.  
- Automate cost optimization reports and dashboards.  

---

## 7. Data Management & Reporting
- Standardize data definitions and naming conventions.  
- Normalize and enrich discovery data.  
- Align software data with CMDB and ITAM datasets.  
- Build executive dashboards and compliance scorecards.  
- Integrate SAM data with BI platforms (Power BI, Tableau, etc.).  
- Perform regular data quality checks and governance reviews.  

---

## 8. Tools & Automation
- Configure and maintain SAM tools (ServiceNow SAM, Flexera, Snow, Lansweeper, etc.).  
- Automate data collection, reconciliation, and reporting.  
- Utilize APIs and scripts (PowerShell, Python) for integrations.  
- Manage tagging standards for automated categorization.  
- Deploy automated workflows for provisioning/deprovisioning.  
- Explore AI/ML-driven insights for predictive SAM analytics.  

---

## 9. Security & Access Control
- Enforce role-based access control (RBAC) for SAM data.  
- Integrate with Identity and Access Management (IAM) solutions.  
- Maintain approved software lists and restrict unauthorized software.  
- Protect license and contract data with encryption and secure storage.  
- Ensure compliance with data protection standards (GDPR, NIST, CIS).  
- Securely decommission and sanitize retired assets.  

---

## 10. Training & Communication
- Provide SAM awareness and compliance training for end users.  
- Educate IT, Finance, and Procurement teams on SAM policies.  
- Publish internal newsletters and knowledge base articles.  
- Develop stakeholder communication plans and reports.  
- Share audit lessons learned and continuous improvement outcomes.  
- Promote a culture of accountability and transparency in software usage.  

